Class DataLayerListenerService

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ComponentCallbacks, ComponentCallbacks2, CapabilityApi.CapabilityListener, ChannelApi.ChannelListener, DataApi.DataListener, MessageApi.MessageListener

    public class DataLayerListenerService
extends WearableListenerService

    Listens for data published through a ChannelClient.Channel by wearable nodes. Received data is published to an MQTT broker in real-time.

    The service is started in the background whenever ChannelClient opens up a channel to the node on which the service is installed. It is likewise stopped when the channel is closed, see WearableListenerService. The channel is either closed by the publishing side or if an error occurs during data processing in this service.

    Messages are separated out of the data stream using a simple custom format. This format is necessary because ChannelClient communicates through InputStream and OutputStream, and therefore does not have the notion of single "messages", but rather operates on a continuous stream of data. See onChannelOpened(ChannelClient.Channel) for more details.

      • stats

        private final Runnable stats

        Calculates the current statistics for the sensor recording session. Invoked through an instance of Handler, posts itself at the end of the method to run repeatedly every DELAY_MILLIS ms.

        See the wearable application documentation for more details, which uses the same logic.

      • onChannelOpened

        public void onChannelOpened(ChannelClient.Channel channel)

        Callback that is executed when the ChannelClient.Channel is opened. Connects to the MQTT broker and initiates processing of the data published by the other node through ChannelClient.

        The connection to the MQTT broker is established through AccountConnector first, which acts as an interface to AccountManager and MqttService. Stored credentials of the account are used to connect to the broker.

        Subsequently, the corresponding InputStream is acquired from the opened ChannelClient.Channel. A success listener is used to start processing the data as soon as the InputStream is ready to use.

        SharedPreferences is used to retrieve the current session ID, which is used as an identifier for the MQTT topics.

        Overrides:
        onChannelOpened in class WearableListenerService
        Parameters:
        channel - See WearableListenerService.onChannelOpened(ChannelClient.Channel)
        See Also:
        WearableListenerService, AccountManager, MqttService, SharedPreferences, ChannelClient

      • readStream

        private void readStream(InputStream inputStream)
                 throws IOException

        Reads the stream of bytes by processing each message.As data is received as a continuous stream of bytes, a simple custom protocol is used to extract separate messages from the stream. The processor reads the stream in chunks of 40 bytes, the maximum size of a message defined by the protocol.

        See the documentation of the publishing side in the wearable application for more details about the protocol.

        Parameters:
        inputStream - Stream of sensor data to be processed
        Throws:
        IOException - if the InputStream was closed on the other side or could not be processed.
